of improved educational outcomes remains enormous interestingly the quantitative difference between an endogenous and neoclassical model framework with improved skills affecting the long run growth rate versus just the steady state income level matters less than academic discussions suggest we close by discussing evidence on which education policy reforms may be able to bring about the simulated improvements in educational outcomes download topics growth economic impact international resources efficiency related the high cost of low educational performance the high cost of low educational performance the long run impact of improving pisa outcomes hoover institution 434 galvez mall room 151 stanford university stanford ca 94305 6010 phone 650.736 0942 fax 650.723 1687 2012 hanushek net questions or comments member log in stanford university
